					clicks into code inside an object.  if I can figure out how
					to do one, should be able to do all of them in similar 
					fashion.  hardest one will be options, since they have several
					components.  text and predicate will be easier, so probably
					want to start with one of them.
					
						-can use .put in a map to match text with values...
							e.g., if they type "x=4", i could use myMap.put(x,4)
							but get the "x" and the "4" from the string...
						-can use an array list of characters, and refer to them
							by index within the text.  need the final version to
							refer to elements of the gamestate.  question is how
							to get them out?  will need to label them within the
							gamestate in a way that lets me get them out (setting
							flags?).  
						-may also want to rethink class definition of events...
							should they be interfaces of functions that get called
							when the game runs them, rather than just having 
							elements in them?  this might make it easier to create 
							them...create as data with a "implement" function,
							which is called at run time to produce the necessary
							fields?  or just use a "getter" that returns text, 
							for example, but use it to generate the text, rather
							than just returning a stored value...
							
