					exception type I was using before, so leads to same invalid state
					as if there is a syntax error in the code, which isn't whati want.
					i could throw a different type of exception, but it'll end up
					in a different catch block, which may lead to real errors being
					missed.  probably actually need to return dummy objects (eg, -999
